<div class="post-576 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-autobiographical tag-hip-hop tag-smashwords tag-steven-hager">
	<h2 id="post-576"><a href="http://stevenhager420.wordpress.com/2012/01/26/hip-hop-on-smashwords/" rel="bookmark">Hip Hop on&nbsp;smashwords</a></h2>
			<p class="comments"><a href="http://stevenhager420.wordpress.com/2012/01/26/hip-hop-on-smashwords/#comments">leave a comment &raquo;</a></p>
	
	<div class="main">
		<p><a href="http://stevenhager420.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/962874118_m.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-577" title="962874118_m" alt="" src="http://stevenhager420.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/962874118_m.jpg?w=700"   /></a>I  recently re-published my first ebook on smashwords.com, which is a little like bandcamp.com in that it makes the process of selling a book so simple anyone with no technical expertise can suddenly create their own fully-loaded commercial website. I highly recommend other authors check out this site. It has loads of free books available and many of the books sell for 99 cents (which is the lowest price they allow). Since the hardback copy of <em>Hip Hop</em> sells for upwards of $500 (when you can find it) being able to download this ebook version (in virtually any format for any viewing device) for $4.99 is a boon to anyone interested in researching the origins of the dominant cultural movement of our time. The book was recently updated with never-before-seen exclusive photos and images, so if you downloaded an earlier version (at a cheaper price), be sure and load this new one for free. That&#8217;s the real beauty of ebooks. They keep getting better and the updated version are always free.</p>
<p>Please visit my smashwords site, most of my ebooks are free to read. Click on the link at the top of the column on the right.</p>
